  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SHO Appeal &#x2013; Vaccination Campaign for Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will be directly implemented by Oxfam as emergency response to COVID19. Oxfam will rehabilitate Water Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) infrastructures in health facilities those are likely to provide COVID19 vaccines. Further, Oxfam will do perception tracking on COVID19 and raise awareness through health messaging. Oxfam has already placed staff and volunteers, those will be trained to implement the project. The hardware will be managed by contractor where Oxfam will ensure technical standards through close monitoring.  Key activities are:  -Rehabilitation of WASH facilities in vaccination points/ Public Health Units (PHUs) including provision of sanitization kits  -Selection &amp; training of Community -based volunteers /  influencers   -Develop campaign products for  C19 Vaccination campaign    - Community -based C19 Vaccination campaign  &amp; perception tracking  -Mass media  C19 Vaccination campaign    -Advocacy, media communication products</narrative>
  </description>
